        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Axillary Staging of Breast Cancer: What the Radiologist Should Know" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jacob S.  Ecanow" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Hiroyuki  Abe" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Gillian M.  Newstead" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="David B.  Ecanow" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jan M.  Jeske" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The role of imaging in evaluating the axilla in patients with early stage invasive breast cancer is discussed, with an emphasis on the essential anatomy, pathologic features, and imaging findings." /><meta name="Description" content="The role of imaging in evaluating the axilla in patients with early stage invasive breast cancer is discussed, with an emphasis on the essential anatomy, pathologic features, and imaging findings." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Identifying the presence of axillary node and internal mammary node metastases in patients with invasive breast cancer is critical for determining prognosis and for deciding on appropriate treatmen..." /><meta name="Description" content="Identifying the presence of axillary node and internal mammary node metastases in patients with invasive breast cancer is critical for determining prognosis and for deciding on appropriate treatmen..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2013-10-01" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="publisher-id" content="125060" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.336125060" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.336125060" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta name="dc.Coverage" content="world" /><meta name="dc.Rights"