egative breast cancer: results from the NSABP B-32 randomised phase III trial. <em>Lancet Oncol</em> 2007;8(10):881–888.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S1470-2045(07)70278-4">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17851130/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Technical+outcomes+of+sentinel-lymph-node+resection+and+conventional+axillary-lymph-node+dissection+in+patients+with+clinically+node-negative+breast+cancer%3A+results+from+the+NSABP+B-32+randomised+phase+III+trial&amp;author=DN+Krag&amp;author=SJ+Anderson&amp;author=TB+Julian&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=Lancet+Oncol&amp;pages=881-888&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS1470-2045%2807%2970278-4&amp;pmid=17851130">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Giuliano AE, Hunt KK, Ballman KV, et al. Axillary dissection vs no axillary dissection in women with invasive breast cancer and sentinel node metastasis: a randomized clinical trial. <em>JAMA</em> 2011;305(6): 569–575.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1001/jama.2011.90">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21304082/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Axillary+dissection+vs+no+axillary+dissection+in+women+with+invasive+breast+cancer+and+sentinel+node+metastasis%3A+a+randomized+clinical+trial&amp;author=AE+Giuliano&amp;author=KK+Hunt&amp;author=KV+Ballman&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=JAMA&amp;pages=569-575&amp;doi=10.1001%2Fjama.2011.90&amp;pmid=21304082">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-ha